ie.cit.group3.utility

Class GeneralFormBackingBean

  • java.lang.Object
    • ie.cit.group3.utility.GeneralFormBackingBean

  • public class GeneralFormBackingBean
extends java.lang.Object
    Author:
    john murphy This class is used for 2 forms(html) as the form backing bean to take user input. 1) Used for taking the 'Browse/Search' options that a user inputs into the 'displayOptions.html' which is located at: {base project URL}/browse/ This form captures the Type of search (on Museum Object or People or Roles or Crowdsourced Descriptions/UserComments/Tagwords), the sub-heading ( if one exists, e.g.: search by Title, search by ID etc), it captures the search criteria, the number of pages to be returned in the search results, the sort direction of the returned search. 2) Used for capturing the Directory to import JSON files from in import.html.
